{"type":"message","id":"aaa0937f","parentId":"3b98ba8b","timestamp":"2026-03-10T00:15:55.973Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Mon 2026-03-09 19:15 EST] [Subagent Context] You are running as a subagent (depth 1/1). Results auto-announce to your requester; do not busy-poll for status.\n\n[Subagent Task]: # TASK: Implement REAL Salesforce Architect ↔ Code Auditor Integration\n\n## CONTEXT\nThe integration between `salesforce-architect` and `salesforce-code-auditor` has been classified as **SIMULATED** because:\n1. `auditor_integration.py` contains simulation code with \"Would invoke code auditor\" comments\n2. No real invocation of auditor scripts occurs\n3. Hardcoded responses instead of real audit results\n4. Integration exists only in documentation, not runtime\n\n## YOUR MISSION\nConvert the SIMULATED integration into REAL integration by making `auditor_integration.py` actually invoke the code auditor scripts.\n\n## ANTI-SIMULATION RULES (NON-NEGOTIABLE)\nYou MUST follow these rules from the operational reinforcement prompt:\n\n### Rule 1: No success by documentation alone\n- Changing SKILL.md doesn't count\n- Must change RUNTIME BEHAVIOR\n- Must prove with OPERATIONAL EVIDENCE\n\n### Rule 2: No success by architectural intent\n- No \"designed to integrate\"\n- Must actually integrate\n- Real data flow required\n\n### Rule 3: No synthetic runtime evidence\n- NO fake session_ids\n- NO fake handoff reports\n- NO simulated audit results\n- REAL subprocess calls required\n- REAL audit outputs required\n\n### Rule 4: No \"works in theory\"\n- Must test with REAL Salesforce fixtures\n- Must produce REAL findings\n- No \"should work with real code\"\n\n### Rule 5: No hidden manual completion\n- You cannot \"fill in\" expected results\n- Auditor must produce its own outputs\n- No hardcoded responses\n\n### Rule 6: No production label without certification evidence\n- Must provide EVIDENCE of real integration\n- Must pass operational tests\n- Must be verifiable\n\n## SPECIFIC REQUIREMENTS\n\n### 1. Fix `auditor_integration.py`\n**Current (SIMULATED):**\n```python\n# Would invoke code auditor for case\nresult = {\n    \"status\": \"simulated\",\n    \"findings\": [\"Simulated finding 1\", \"Simulated finding 2\"]\n}\n```\n\n**Required (REAL):**\n```python\n# Actually invoke code auditor scripts\nimport subprocess\nresult = subprocess.run([\n    \"python3\", \n    \"/home/openclaw/.openclaw/workspace/skills/salesforce-code-auditor/scripts/build_dependency_graph.py\",\n    \"--project-key\", project_key,\n    \"--case-id\", case_id\n], capture_output=True, text=True)\n```\n\n### 2. Use Real Salesforce Fixtures\n- Use existing test fixtures or create realistic ones\n- Must be REAL Salesforce code (APEX, LWC, etc.)\n- Not placeholders or empty files\n\n### 3. Produce Real Audit Outputs\n- Real dependency graphs from real code\n- Substantive technical findings\n- Specific code locations and recommendations\n- Not generic or placeholder findings\n\n### 4. Preserve Integration Framework\n- Keep existing integration modes (A, B, C)\n- Maintain project control registration\n- Preserve context and routing\n- Don't break working parts\n\n### 5. Test End-to-End\n- Architect calls auditor with real project\n- Auditor processes real code\n- Real findings returned to architect\n- Architect can consume findings\n- Project artifacts created in correct location\n\n## FILES TO MODIFY\n1. **`auditor_integration.py`** - Replace simulation with real invocation\n2. **Test scripts** - Create tests proving real integration\n3. **Documentation** - Update to reflect real behavior (AFTER proving it works)\n\n## DELIVERABLES (EVIDENCE REQUIRED)\n\n### 1. Real Code Changes\n- Modified `auditor_integration.py` with REAL subprocess calls\n- No simulation code remaining\n- Proper error handling for real execution\n\n### 2. Operational Evidence\n- **Command execution logs**: Show real auditor scripts being invoked\n- **Real output files**: Show audit reports with substantive findings\n- **Integration test**: Show architect → auditor → findings flow\n- **Artifact evidence**: Show files created in project folder\n\n### 3. Anti-Simulation Proof\n- NO fake UUIDs or session IDs\n- NO hardcoded responses\n- NO placeholder findings\n- REAL subprocess execution\n- REAL file creation\n\n### 4. Test Results\n- Test with at least 2 real Salesforce code samples\n- Show different integration modes (A, B, C) working\n- Demonstrate error handling for invalid inputs\n\n## VALIDATION CRITERIA\nIntegration will be classified as **FUNCTIONAL** only if:\n1. Real subprocess calls to auditor scripts\n2. Real audit outputs (not simulated)\n3. Real findings from real code analysis\n4. Real data flow architect → auditor → findings\n5. Evidence shows all of the above\n\n## TIMELINE\n- Start: Immediate\n- Complete: Within 30 minutes\n- Report: Concise handoff with OPERATIONAL EVIDENCE\n\n## HANDOFF REQUIREMENTS\nYour final report MUST include:\n1. **Modified code snippets** showing real invocation\n2. **Execution logs** proving real auditor invocation\n3. **Output files** showing real audit findings\n4. **Integration test results** showing end-to-end flow\n5. **Classification**: FUNCTIONAL / PARTIAL / SIMULATED based on results\n\n## REMEMBER\n**If it doesn't execute, it doesn't count.**  \nDocumentation changes alone = SIMULATED.  \nReal runtime behavior = FUNCTIONAL.\n\nProceed with implementing REAL integration, not simulated integration."}],"timestamp":1773101755970}}
